# Theme System Rules

## üî¥ CRITICAL: Never Hardcode Colors

This is a multi-tenant platform. Each salon has its own theme.
ALL colors must come from theme tokens.

## How to Use Theme Colors

### Method 1: Inline Styles (Preferred)

```typescript
import { themeVars } from '@/theme';

// ‚úÖ CORRECT
style={{ 
  backgroundColor: themeVars.primary,
  color: themeVars.titleText,
  borderColor: themeVars.cardBorder,
}}

// For gradients
style={{
  background: `linear-gradient(to right, ${themeVars.primary}, ${themeVars.primaryDark})`,
}}

// For transparency
style={{
  backgroundColor: `color-mix(in srgb, ${themeVars.primary} 20%, transparent)`,
}}
```

### Method 2: Tailwind Arbitrary Values

```typescript
// ‚úÖ CORRECT
className="bg-[var(--theme-primary)]"
className="text-[var(--theme-accent)]"
className="border-[var(--theme-card-border)]"
```

## ‚ùå NEVER Do This

```typescript
// ‚ùå WRONG - Hardcoded hex
style={{ backgroundColor: '#f4b864' }}
className="bg-[#f4b864]"

// ‚ùå WRONG - Tailwind color classes for brand colors
className="bg-amber-400"
className="text-purple-600"
className="border-amber-200"
```

## Available Theme Tokens

| Token | CSS Variable | Usage |
|-------|-------------|-------|
| `themeVars.primary` | `--theme-primary` | Buttons, accents |
| `themeVars.primaryDark` | `--theme-primary-dark` | Selection rings |
| `themeVars.accent` | `--theme-accent` | Page titles |
| `themeVars.background` | `--theme-background` | Page bg |
| `themeVars.cardBackground` | `--theme-card-background` | Cards |
| `themeVars.cardBorder` | `--theme-card-border` | Card borders |
| `themeVars.selectedBackground` | `--theme-selected-background` | Selected items |
| `themeVars.selectedRing` | `--theme-selected-ring` | Selection rings |
| `themeVars.titleText` | `--theme-title-text` | Page titles |
| `themeVars.highlightBackground` | `--theme-highlight-background` | Points |

## Adding New Theme Colors

If you need a new semantic color:

1. Add to `src/theme/theme.types.ts` in ThemeColors interface
2. Add value to `src/theme/themes.ts` in nailSalonNo5Theme
3. Add CSS variable mapping in `src/theme/ThemeProvider.tsx`
4. Add to themeVars object in ThemeProvider.tsx

Never skip these steps and use hardcoded colors instead.
